label.value: normal number of Rad52 foci during mitotic S phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Rad52 (also called Rad22) accumulates is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during S phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: decreased microtubule polymerization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule polymerization, i.e. the addition of tubulin dimers, occurs to a lesser extent than normal.

label.value: decreased microtubule depolymerization during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule depolymerization, i.e. the removal of tubulin dimers, occurs to a lesser extent than normal.

label.value: increased duration of mitotic prophase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of progression through prophase of mitosis is longer than normal.

label.value: increased duration of mitotic prometaphase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of progression through prometaphase of mitosis is longer than normal.

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to cadmium ion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to cadmium ions is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: microtubule bundles present in decreased numbers during mitotic interphase

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain fewer microtubule bundles than normal during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: eMTOC absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cell does not contain a detectable equatorial microtubule organizing center (eMTOC).

label.value: normal astral microtubules

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount, distribution, and morphology of astral microtubules is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: inviable binucleate aseptate cell with mitotic cell cycle arrest before cell separation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is inviable and has two nuclei but no septum, and the mitotic cell cycle is arrested before cell separation takes place.

definition.value: This phenotype may indicate that the cytokinesis after mitosis checkpoint is activated.

label.value: abnormal eMTOC assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which equatorial microtubule organizing center (eMTOC) assembly is abnormal. eMTOC assembly is the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an equatorial microtubule organizing center.

label.value: decreased spindle pole body-led chromosome movement during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the mitotic spindle pole body (SPB) moves rapidly back and forth to a lower extent and over a smaller area than normal, causing decreased chromosome movement. Normally, SPB oscillation occurs during mitotic interphase (as well as prophase) but is restricted to a small space.

label.value: abnormal microtubule nucleation during vegetative growth

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of microtubules from one or more microtubule organizing centers (MTOCs) is abnormal.

label.value: abolished cytoplasmic microtubule nucleation

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of cytoplasmic microtubules from one or more microtubule organizing centers (MTOCs) is does not occur.

label.value: decreased interphase microtubule nucleation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of cytoplasmic microtubules occurs to a lower extent than normal during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: abolished astral microtubule nucleation during mitosis

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of astral microtubules from the spindle pole body does not occur during mitosis.

label.value: abolished cytoplasmic microtubule nucleation from iMTOC

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of cytoplasmic microtubules from the interphase microtubule organizing center does not occur. Normally, microtubules are nucleated from interphase microtubule organizing centers (iMTOCs) and from the cytoplasmic face of the spindle pole body (SPB).

label.value: abolished cytoplasmic interphase microtubule nucleation from spindle pole body

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of cytoplasmic microtubules from the spindle pole body (SPB) does not occur during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. Normally, microtubules are nucleated from interphase microtubule organizing centers (iMTOCs) and from the cytoplasmic face of the SPB.

label.value: abolished microtubule nucleation from eMTOC

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of microtubules from the equatorial microtubule organizing center does not occur.

label.value: normal interphase microtubule nucleation from spindle pole body

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of cytoplasmic microtubules from the spindle pole body (SPB) normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: abolished protein localization to eMTOC

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the equatorial microtubule organizing center (eMTOC) does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to iMTOC

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the interphase microtubule organizing center does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to microtubule organizing center

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to one or more microtubule organizing centers is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased rate of microtubule polymerization during vegetative growth

value.value: A  microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule polymerization, i.e. the addition of tubulin dimers to the plus end of a microtubule, occurs at a lower rate, or speed, than normal.

label.value: loss of viability following cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable after exposure to hydroxyurea.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown in the presence of hydroxyurea, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon hydroxyurea removal is measured and compared to wild type.

label.value: loss of viability following cellular response to UV

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable after exposure to ultraviolet light.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown with exposure to UV light, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon return to absence of UV is measured and compared to wild type.

label.value: increased duration of mitotic anaphase B

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of progression through anaphase B of mitosis is longer than normal. Anaphase B is the stage of mitosis in which the polar microtubules elongate and the two poles of the spindle move farther apart.

label.value: normal protein localization to eMTOC

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the equatorial microtubule organizing center (eMTOC) is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to iMTOC

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the interphase microtubule organizing center (iMTOC) is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of DNA replication initiation resulting in complete rereplication, with mitotic cell cycle arrest

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which negative regulation of the initiation of DNA-dependent DNA replication is abnormal, resulting in one or more rounds of rereplication of the entire genome, followed by cell cycle arrest.

label.value: decreased cyclin B1-CDK1 complex level

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain fewer protein complexes consisting of cyclin B1 and cyclin-dependent kinase 1 (CDK1) than normal.

label.value: sensitive to Cutin-1

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to Cutin-1 (N-carbamoyl-2-(triphenyl-lambda-5-phosphanylidene)acetamide). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of Cutin-1 that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: abolished cytokinesis checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which cell cycle regulation mediated by the mitotic cytokinesis checkpoint does not occur under conditions that normally trigger the checkpoint signaling and response. Normally, the cytokinesis checkpoint normally delays the G2/M transition of a mitotic cell cycle if cytokinesis was not completed correctly in the previous cell cycle.

label.value: premature protein localization to nucleolus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleolus begins earlier than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed activation of protein kinase activity during mitosis

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which activation of an inactive protein kinase activity begins later than normal during mitosis.

label.value: delayed negative regulation of protein kinase activity during mitosis

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which negative regulation of a protein kinase activity begins later than normal during mitosis.

label.value: normal protein kinase activity during mitosis

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a protein kinase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during mitosis.

label.value: decreased protein kinase activity during mitosis

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a protein kinase activity is decreased during mitosis.

label.value: abolished mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromosome recapture does not occur during metaphase of mitosis. Chromosome recapture is the reattachment of chromosomes which have become detached from the spindle.

label.value: normal mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromosome recapture is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during metaphase of mitosis. Chromosome recapture is the reattachment of chromosomes which have become detached from the spindle.

label.value: curved mitotic spindle during anaphase B

value.value: A spindle phenotype in which the mitotic spindle is curved (i.e. follows a smooth bend rather than a straight line) during anaphase B.

label.value: mitotic spindle collapse during anaphase B elongation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a mitotic spindle assembles and begins to elongate, but becomes curved during anaphase B and eventually collapses. The spindle pole bodies separate, but often become spatially closer together as the spindle elongates and curves.

label.value: abnormal protein methyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of protein methyltransferase activity is abnormal.

label.value: increased protein methyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of protein methyltransferase activity is increased.

label.value: decreased protein methyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of protein methyltransferase activity is decreased.

label.value: abolished deactivation of mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which deactivation of the mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint does not occur. The mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint normally delays the metaphase/anaphase transition of a mitotic nuclear division until the spindle is correctly assembled and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

definition.value: The difference between this term and constitutive activation of mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint (FYPO:000) is that this term describes cells in which the checkpoint is not active at first, but once activated the checkpoint is not deactivated, whereas FYPO:0007 describes cells in which the checkpoint is always active, i.e. the checkpoint is never observed to be "off". Checkpoint activation in a mutant usually implies that the mutation is causing problems that the checkpoint detects.

label.value: decreased rate of deactivation of mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which deactivation of the mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint occurs more slowly than normal. The mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint normally delays the metaphase/anaphase transition of a mitotic nuclear division until the spindle is correctly assembled and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

definition.value: Checkpoint activation in a mutant usually implies that the mutation is causing problems that the checkpoint detects.

label.value: normal deactivation of mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which deactivation of the mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type. The mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint normally delays the metaphase/anaphase transition of a mitotic nuclear division until the spindle is correctly assembled and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

definition.value: Checkpoint activation in a mutant usually implies that the mutation is causing problems that the checkpoint detects.

label.value: increased cellular ferrichrome level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more ferrichromes measured in a cell is higher than normal.
